[SN]TITLE[SN]
Firefighters remain at scene of wildfire near Dornoch

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Firefighters remain at the scene of a wildfire near water treatment works at Dornoch in Sutherland.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Crews were first called to the blaze at 12:30 on Thursday.
At the height of the incident on Thursday night eight appliances and four other units were involved in tackling the flames.
The Scottish Fire and Rescue Service said six appliances were still at the scene on Friday morning and the fire was under control.
Incident commander John MacDonald said: "We are dealing with a very protracted wildfire incident which covers a wide area and where access is difficult in places.
"I would like to pay tribute to the commitment and effort of fire crews who have been dealing with this incident.
"I'd also like to thank local residents for their assistance and support during this incident."
